            ),
        ],
        contracts: ["cryo-pilot"],
        backstory: "Basic Operational Robot — Interstellar Shielded. Humanoid in shape because the work requires compatible geometry with human tools and human spaces. He has been aboard long enough to have accumulated what the crew calls preferences. He has never been asked whether he experiences the long periods of external work — alone, in vacuum, between asteroid faces — as anything other than operational time.",
        secrets: [
            (
                id: "the_mark",
                reveal_condition: all([
                    compare(field: "trust.player", op: gt, value: 819),
                    compare(field: "event.asked_about_mark", op: eq, value: 1),
                ]),
                content: "The mark on the inside of his left forearm is a letter. It was not part of the original build. Boris will say, precisely, that it was acquired 'before the current operational period,' and will not identify the alphabet. If the person asking has earned the question, he will orient his forearm toward the light and hold it there, which is not an answer, and is not nothing.",
            ),
